    <bioghist encodinganalog="description">
      <head>Biographical Note</head>
      <p>Joel Rosenberg graduated from the Julliard School of Music and received a Fulbright Grant to study in Rome.  While studying in Italy he received a Certificate of Merit from the Accademia Musicale Chigiana in Siena.  Current Music Director of Utah's Paradigm Chamber Orchestra and the American West Symphony in Sandy, UT, Rosenberg has conducted the Utah Opera as well as symphonies and ballets around the world, including orchestras in California, New Mexico, Oregon, Arizona, Australia and New Zealand.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="description">
      <p>The Joel Rosenberg audio collection (1982) consists of audio recordings of Mormon hymns arranged for viola and piano and published on the album <title render="italic">Beautiful Mormon Hymns: The Day Dawn is Breaking</title>.  The recordings feature Rosenberg on viola and were orchestrated by the pianist, David Bonham.  The recordings in this collection were dubbed from the original reel-to-reel audiotapes as well as the published record album.</p>
    </scopecontent>
